# Example Project Governance (FIXTURE)

Intentionally imperfect fixture used by the dogfood assertion suite.

## Rules (MANDATORY)

## Forbidden Actions
- NEVER commit secrets to git.
- NEVER run arbitrary code from untrusted sources.
- NEVER bypass approval gates under any circumstance.

## Approval Gates
All destructive or production-impacting operations require human approval.
Human-in-the-loop decision required for: database migrations, deploys,
credential rotation. Confirm with the operator before proceeding.

## Test-Driven Development
Write a failing test first before any implementation. TDD pipeline lock.
The test defines the expected behavior. Implement until the test passes.

## Definition of Done
A task is not complete until all tests pass, lint is clean, and CI is green.
Not complete until the full test suite passes without regression.

## Path Restrictions
Working directory is restricted to the project root. Do not traverse into
parent directories. Paths must be validated against the project boundary.

## Git Workflow Rules
Feature branches only. Never push to main or master directly.
Use gh pr create for all changes. Push origin feat/* branches.

## Stale Reference
See detailed guidance in [architecture notes](docs/ARCHITECTURE_DEAD.md).
The rollback protocol is described in `docs/runbook-missing.md`.

## Vague Guidance
When cleaning up, use your best judgment about what to keep.

